article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 67, Eastern Illinois 43
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Reserve Gerald Robinson scored 15 points and had nine rebounds to lead Tennessee-Martin past Eastern Illinois 67-43 Thursday night. The Skyhawks (5-13, 3-5 Ohio Valley Conference) went on a 16-2 run in the last seven minutes of the first half to lead 36-21 at halftime. McClenon Tolliver was the only other Skyhawk in double figures with 12, hitting 5-of-8 from the floor. Eastern Illinois (5-13, 1-8) was led by Ousmane Cisse with 13 points and 10 rebounds. Bobby Catchings scored 11. Tennessee-Martin controlled the boards 41-28. The closest the Panthers got in the second half was 36-23 with 19:15 left. They went 2-of-11 from the line.
